HEADWORD: Yellowthroat
<hw>Yel"low*throat`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any one of several species of American ground warblers of the genus
<gen>Geothlypis</gen>, esp. the Maryland yellowthroat (<spn>Geothlypis
trichas</spn>), which is a very common species.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

